## Disclaimer
This repository is a **simplified** and reproducible demonstration of a methodology.
All data are simulated  for educational purposes. The views expressed here are personal
and do not represent ANStat, OSEP, or any public institution. No confidential or proprietary data are included.


## Code Structure – INQSP Methodology Demo
This folder contains the full Stata pipeline used to compute a simplified and reproducible version of the Public Service Quality Index (INQSP).
All scripts are written using relative paths to ensure portability and reproducibility across systems.

File Structure
00_setup.do

Initializes the working environment:
Defines global paths (data, output, code)
Creates output subfolders
Ensures Stata is launched from the repository root
This script must be executed before any analytical file.

00_master.do

Master execution file:
Calls 00_setup.do
Executes analytical scripts in the correct order
Produces final outputs
Recommended entry point for full replication.

01_Quality_of_transformation_initiatives.do

Computes:

Sub-index 1: Existence of operational mechanisms
Sub-index 2: Appropriation of the “Fonctionnaire Nouveau” concept
Final index 1  (equal weighting)  

02_Quality_of_services_received.do


...



Technical Requirements
Stata 17 or higher
No external packages required
